<div id="page-header">
  <h1>Committee Member Dashboard</h1>
</div>
<body>
  <div id="chart-description">
    <h4>This graph displays the relationships between faculty departments of graduate student committees and graduate
    student programs at Penn State. You are able to filter this information by the college or campus of your selection
    in the dropdown below. You can then see the departments of various committee members and which graduate students'
    programs they served on a committee. For example, filtering by College of Engineering will display the faculty
    departments in that college, and all of the graduate studentsâ€™ departments for the committees they have served on.</h4>
    <h4><strong>Click on a the committee member department </strong>to view the number of students associated with that department or</h4>
    <h4><strong>Click on the program </strong>to view the number of committee member departments associated with that program.</h4>
    <h4>This information is gathered from <a href="https://submit-etda.libraries.psu.edu/main">Penn State University Libraries ETDA system</a> from 1999 to present day.</h4>
  </div>
    <div id="college-dropdown-container" class="col-12">
    <label for="college-select">Select Committee Member College:</label>
    <select id="college-select">
      <% @colleges.each_with_index do |college, index| %>
        <option value="<%= college %>" <%= 'selected="selected"' if index.zero? %>><%= college %></option>
      <% end %>
    </select>
    <h2><div id="college-title" class="text-center"></div></h2>
  </div>
  <div class="col-6">
    <div id="department-header" class="p-5 text-center">
      <h2>Committee Member Department:</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-6">
    <div id="program-header" class="p-5 text-center">
      <h2>Student Program:</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div id="network-graph" data='<%= raw @committee_member_data.to_json %>'></div>
  <div id="bar-chart"></div>
</body>
